Commentary Text: Holder to Riyan Parag, out Caught by Warner!! Bowling is all about watching what the batsman does at the crease till the last moment. Bumrah, Malinga, Starc... They'll tell you the importance of it. Holder saw Parag move across and give the charge, so banged the slower ball short and forced him to fetch, shows how shrewd he is as a cricketer, Parag in no position to fetch that hit, skied it high, Warner ran back from mid-off, caught that, but it popped, reacted quickly to juggle and clutch it onto his chest and pouch as he was falling back. Riyan Parag c Warner b Holder 20(12) [4s-2 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Holder to Samson, out Bowled!! Oh no! The jinx! Don't blame me, I am equally disappointed as Samson, who walks away livid with himself. Holder took pace off and hit the short of length zone, Samson went back giving room and looking to cut late, but missed and the ball hit the top of the poles. Commentary Text: Rashid Khan to Stokes, 2 runs, oh dear! Vijay Shankar has dropped Stokes. Stokes waltzed down the pitch and decided to go after Rashid with a slog over mid-wicket. No timing behind it and almost paid the price. He is living a charmed life. Vijay Shankar ran across to his right and got both hands to it, but the ball popped put of his hand because of what probably looked like an unnecessary last minute jump to grab when he could have normally run and stretched to take the catch. He tries to take it on the second attempt with a forward-dive, but it was out of his reach..

Commentary Text: Holder to Stokes, out Uthappa Run Out!! Oh dear! An unfortunate end to Uthappa's knock who was looking in good touch, Stokes gets cramped by this 132.6kph in-seamer and struck around the hip region (via an inside edge). The ball dies down adjacent to the pitch on the off-side and Uthappa is halfway down. The single wasn't on and even Stokes was never interested. Holder was quick to get to the ball, he turned and hit the bullseye to catch Uthappa short of his crease. The non-striker was also late to turn back. SRH get the lucky breakthrough! Uthappa run out (Holder) 19(13) [4s-2 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Jofra Archer to Bairstow, out Bowled!! Boom! 149kph, bullet, an in-ducker and Bairstow has no answers. Archer wins the battle against his England team-mate. SRH in a pickle with both openers back in the shed. Archer on song as RR have their tails up. It was the in-ducker, Bairstow's feet were frozen. Probably, didn't expect it to nip back into him. Has a mere push, huge gap between bat and pad, it sneaks through the gate after beating the inside edge and kisses the top of middle. Magical delivery, how do you play those? But this was the ideal length to Bairstow - just kept it full and got the reward. The sheer joy on Archer's face, wow! Bairstow b Jofra Archer 10(7) [4s-1 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Jofra Archer to Warner, out Caught by Stokes!! There you go! Someone please see if Archer has a tweet for this event. Wow! Raw pace and Warner is sent packing. Lethal from Jofraa.
